Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State, on Monday sacked Mr Augustine Pelemo, his Special Assistant on Political Matters. This was disclosed in a statement by Mr Donald Ojogo, the State Commissioner for Information, on Monday in Akure He said the sack was with immediate effect, NAN reports. He explained that the directive underscored the need to instil sanity and nip in the bud divisive acts and tendencies inimical to the existing cordiality and cohesion in the state administration. Ojogo said the governor had directed Pelemo to hand over government property in his possession to the Deputy Chief of Staff and wished him well in his future endeavours. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.